      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(agent): dampen Discord stale thread replies",
        "body": "## Summary\n- add Discord-specific message-tool-only guidance only for Discord group/channel turns\n- thread canonical chat type through queued, embedded, and compaction prompt paths\n- cover group/channel positives, direct-message negatives, queued run creation, and runner forwarding\n\n## Diagnosis\nThis was not a Twilio delivery bug. In a Discord thread where final assistant text is private, the runtime correctly exposed `message(action=send)` as the visible reply path. The prompt guidance needed to make the channel-noise tradeoff explicit, but only for Discord group/channel contexts. Direct messages should not receive stale-thread quiet-etiquette guidance.\n\nThe follow-up `check-test-types` CI failure was related: the new queued-run assertion exposed that `FollowupRun.run` did not type or forward the normalized `chatType` through the normal reply runner path.\n\n## Tests\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/agents/system-prompt.test.ts`\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/auto-reply/reply/get-reply-run.media-only.test.ts`\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/auto-reply/reply/agent-runner-utils.test.ts`\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/agents/embedded-agent-runner/run.overflow-compaction.test.ts`\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/agents/embedded-agent-runner/compaction-runtime-context.test.ts`\n- `node --import tsx scripts/generate-prompt-snapshots.ts --check`\n- `node scripts/run-tsgo.mjs -p tsconfig.core.json --incremental --tsBuildInfoFile .artifacts/tsgo-cache/core-pr-91962-followup.tsbuildinfo`\n- `node scripts/run-tsgo.mjs -p test/tsconfig/tsconfig.core.test.json --incremental --tsBuildInfoFile .artifacts/tsgo-cache/core-test-pr-91962.tsbuildinfo`\n- `node scripts/run-oxlint.mjs src/auto-reply/reply/agent-runner-utils.ts src/auto-reply/reply/followup-runner.ts src/auto-reply/reply/agent-runner-utils.test.ts src/auto-reply/reply/queue/types.ts`\n- `.agents/skills/autoreview/scripts/autoreview --mode local`\n\nNot tested: live Discord transcript proof. Remote `check:changed` proof was attempted but blocked by local Crabbox/Testbox setup and missing cloud credentials.\n",
